This app is useful on the occasion when I oversleep and miss the bus. I just wish they wouldn't use push notifications for advertising their deals. I don't like it when they randomly ding my phone throughout the day. Yes, I know I can turn off notifications, and I do. Then I need to turn them back on when I'm using it. I'd rather not have to do this. That's my only gripe with the app. I've never had a bad driver, and they always get me there on time for a reasonable price.

Check your credit/debit card a week or two AFTER you ride. Uber charged me an extra 20$ on a 7$ ride for a "fee adjustment" weeks after I took a ride, without giving me a warning or reason for the adjustment. I asked support about it and they said it's been too long since the trip for them to look at it and give a refund. If you use Uber go over the charges to your card and Uber activity every week to be sure they aren't stealing from you with "fee adjustments". I will never use Uber again

The Uber app works properly and well. We tested it in England, Spain, France, and Brazil. Also the Uber customer service, which we had to contact once or twice is excellent, quick, and very customer centered. Maybe I am doing something wrong but what I miss is that on arrival the final charged price is clearly shown to me. Because once or twice the final price was higher than at the moment of booking and I just saw it after leaving the car and after tipping. Hence no chance to ask the driver.
